  "text": "Proof. For \u03c7 \u2208 S 1 (H) we denote by U\u03c7(H) the stabilizer subgroup of \u03c7 w.r.t. this quotient action. U\u03c7(H) is a closed subgroup of U (H) and a Banach Lie group with Lie algebra the subspace of antiselfadjoint bounded operators commuting with the one dimensional proiection operator P \u03c7 on the ray generated by \u03c7. In fact, Lie(U\u03c7(H)) is a splitting subspace of u(H), so that U\u03c7(H) is a Lie subgroup of U (H). If one changes the vector \u03c7, one obtains a conjugate Lie group. Then by standard arguments P(H) is diffeomorphic to the orbit space U (H)/U\u03c7(H) [CITATION_1] . We also remark that the projection operator in u(H) with range Lie(U\u03c7(H))",
